WEBVTT

00:31.379 --> 00:40.170
[♪♪♪]

00:47.830 --> 00:50.702
[GIRL SCREAMING]

00:50.833 --> 00:59.755
[♪♪♪♪]

01:05.891 --> 01:14.813
[♪♪♪]

01:44.321 --> 01:53.200
[♪♪♪]

01:59.380 --> 02:08.171
[♪♪♪]

02:49.995 --> 02:54.696
Oh! It's beautiful.

02:55.479 --> 02:57.177
You were right, baby.

02:57.307 --> 03:06.186
[♪♪♪♪]

03:47.966 --> 03:51.013
Remember this place?

03:55.887 --> 03:57.889
Huh? Do you remember?

04:16.560 --> 04:25.395
[♪♪♪]

04:36.928 --> 04:38.147
Hello!

04:39.017 --> 04:40.932
Mr. Brookes

04:41.063 --> 04:42.499
Just Brookes.

04:42.630 --> 04:44.632
Nice to meet you.
I'm Sofia.

04:44.762 --> 04:46.590
Nice to meet you.

04:50.028 --> 04:52.117
Uh, I'll get your bags.

05:02.606 --> 05:05.043
I'll show you around.

05:05.174 --> 05:06.828
Housekeeper quit,
sorry about that.

05:06.958 --> 05:07.916
My sister can help.

05:08.046 --> 05:10.048
She's uh-- she's not much
of a cook,

05:10.179 --> 05:12.224
but she'll keep things tidy.

05:13.487 --> 05:15.140
We'll be okay, thank you.

05:15.271 --> 05:16.881
BROOKES:
Okay, well, uh,
whatever you need.

05:28.284 --> 05:32.593
This is you, isn't it?
And your grandma.

05:32.723 --> 05:41.558
[♪♪♪♪]

05:44.518 --> 05:45.997
BROOKES:
Still selling?

05:46.128 --> 05:48.696
It's in probate.

05:48.826 --> 05:51.046
Till you get better, right?

05:54.658 --> 05:56.138
You gonna be okay?
Just you and him?

05:56.268 --> 05:58.358
Yes.

05:58.488 --> 06:07.367
[♪♪♪♪]

06:09.194 --> 06:11.762
BROOKES:
Uh, you'll get all kind of
weird shit up here.

06:14.069 --> 06:16.071
You still sleep together?

06:18.290 --> 06:21.119
The bags. Same room?

06:21.250 --> 06:23.208
-Yes.
-Okay.

06:23.339 --> 06:32.261
[♪♪♪♪]

06:53.369 --> 07:02.291
[♪♪♪]

07:31.886 --> 07:33.148
Hey, Em.

07:33.278 --> 07:35.150
EMILY ON PHONE:
You've been avoiding my calls.

07:35.280 --> 07:37.065
I knew you'd say that.

07:37.195 --> 07:38.719
EMILY ON PHONE:
Did they say you can go?

07:38.849 --> 07:40.503
The doctors can go
fuck themselves.

07:41.722 --> 07:42.766
EMILY ON PHONE:
They got him stable.

07:42.897 --> 07:44.507
It's been a year.

07:44.638 --> 07:47.423
They've given up on him.

07:47.554 --> 07:50.165
It only takes one memory,
who said that?

07:50.295 --> 07:51.949
One memory, to get him started.

07:52.080 --> 07:53.603
EMILY ON PHONE:
You're in trouble
if you're quoting me.

07:53.734 --> 07:55.910
Well, you're the expert.

07:56.040 --> 07:58.042
Em, it's Alex.

08:00.175 --> 08:01.481
He'd rather be dead
than live like this,

08:01.611 --> 08:02.525
you know that.

08:02.656 --> 08:11.491
[♪♪♪♪]

08:17.627 --> 08:26.506
[♪♪♪]

08:43.523 --> 08:45.568
So tomorrow, we'll take a walk.

08:45.699 --> 08:47.875
See if you remember something.

08:54.490 --> 08:59.974
You can still hear me, right?
I know you can.

09:02.890 --> 09:08.156
You're gonna be okay, Alex
We're gonna get you there.

09:08.286 --> 09:09.461
Yeah.

09:18.514 --> 09:20.429
Come on, baby.

09:22.562 --> 09:23.911
Babe?

09:26.957 --> 09:28.350
It's okay.

09:28.480 --> 09:37.359
[♪♪♪♪]

09:45.280 --> 09:49.066
It's okay, baby.
It's just me.

09:50.981 --> 09:51.808
Hmm.

09:57.553 --> 09:58.772
Sleep well.

09:58.902 --> 10:07.824
[♪♪♪♪]

10:17.094 --> 10:19.009
Can't buy taste.

10:49.474 --> 10:50.954
SOFIA:
You got the call?

10:51.085 --> 10:52.652
ALEX:
I got the call.

10:52.782 --> 10:55.132
SOFIA:
And?

10:55.263 --> 10:56.960
Jesus, Alex!
Please, come on?

10:57.091 --> 10:58.788
[ALEX LAUGHS]

10:58.919 --> 11:00.921
ALEX:
Okay, they're in. They're in.

11:01.051 --> 11:02.749
The whole way.
We did it.

11:04.402 --> 11:06.317
So, you gonna come
celebrate with us?

11:06.448 --> 11:08.537
SOFIA:
God, yes.

11:08.668 --> 11:09.320
Love you so much, baby.

11:09.451 --> 11:10.757
ALEX:
I love you.

11:10.887 --> 11:15.370
This is a good day for our lab,
a great day.

11:15.500 --> 11:19.896
I would like to say a special
thank you to my wonderful wife,

11:20.027 --> 11:21.506
a better scientist than all.

11:21.637 --> 11:23.204
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

11:23.334 --> 11:25.119
SOFIA:
I'm so proud of you.

11:26.816 --> 11:28.078
ALEX:
Call in sick.

11:28.252 --> 11:31.212
SOFIA:
I can't, you know I can't.
I'm teaching.

11:31.342 --> 11:33.997
ALEX:
You choose a day at work
over a day with me?

11:34.128 --> 11:36.217
It's not a choice,
it's my job.

11:36.347 --> 11:37.740
Doesn't matter.

11:37.871 --> 11:39.786
SOFIA:
'‘Cause I'm not on the cover
of TechInvest?

11:39.916 --> 11:43.267
But you're not.
Are you?

11:43.398 --> 11:44.529
Now, you're being a dick.

11:44.660 --> 11:46.357
Seriously?

11:46.488 --> 11:47.228
-Don't!
-[VEHICLE HONK]

11:47.358 --> 11:48.577
-[GASPS]
-[THUDS]

11:53.930 --> 12:02.765
[♪♪♪]

12:24.004 --> 12:32.795
[♪♪♪]

12:50.247 --> 12:51.031
[LIGHTER FLICKS]

12:51.161 --> 12:54.034
[TAKES A DRAG]

13:06.394 --> 13:09.223
[TAKES A DRAG]

13:15.533 --> 13:18.275
[FOOTFALLS APPROACHING
IN DISTANCE]

14:04.800 --> 14:07.716
Babe, did you just go
to the bathroom?

14:07.847 --> 14:09.718
Alex?

14:17.160 --> 14:18.031
[SOFIA CHUCKLES]

14:18.161 --> 14:21.295
Sofia, are you high?

14:21.425 --> 14:30.304
[♪♪♪♪]

14:51.412 --> 15:00.334
[♪♪♪]

15:28.710 --> 15:33.410
"“Calvin DuBose, 1937."”

15:33.541 --> 15:42.506
[♪♪♪♪]

15:49.644 --> 15:51.428
SOFIA:
What the fuck?

15:51.559 --> 16:00.394
[♪♪♪♪]

16:04.746 --> 16:06.661
EMILY ON PHONE:
A little, maybe.

16:06.791 --> 16:08.837
A little?

16:08.968 --> 16:11.535
EMILY ON PHONE:
I mean,
there's a resemblance, yeah.

16:11.666 --> 16:13.276
Em, are you kidding me?

16:13.407 --> 16:14.712
It's-- it's him.

16:16.671 --> 16:17.367
EMILY ON PHONE:
Okay, hang on.

16:17.498 --> 16:18.542
Let me get my glasses.

16:18.673 --> 16:19.369
No, no, no.
It's okay.

16:19.500 --> 16:20.892
Trust me. It's Alex.

16:21.067 --> 16:23.286
Just, uh,
look under the signature.

16:24.679 --> 16:25.680
I-- I can't read that, honey.

16:25.810 --> 16:26.986
What does it say?

16:27.116 --> 16:28.291
SOFIA:
1937.

16:28.422 --> 16:30.076
EMILY ON PHONE:
That's when it was painted?

16:30.206 --> 16:34.645
Yeah, and on the back it says
"“Calvin DuBose Self-Portrait"”.

16:34.776 --> 16:37.909
So what you're seeing
is a family thing, yeah?

16:38.040 --> 16:39.389
No.

16:39.520 --> 16:41.522
Um, I'm seeing Alex.

16:41.652 --> 16:42.827
-You just said--
-I-- I know.

16:42.958 --> 16:46.179
It can't be, but...

16:46.309 --> 16:47.745
It is.

16:51.706 --> 16:54.622
[GASPING]

17:02.543 --> 17:05.415
[INDISTINCT RAPPING]

17:05.546 --> 17:14.424
[♪♪♪♪]

17:34.662 --> 17:37.491
[INDISTINCT RAPPING]

17:50.982 --> 17:59.861
[♪♪♪]

18:07.477 --> 18:09.262
Are you fucking with me,
Alex DuBose?

18:09.392 --> 18:10.959
Huh?

18:13.831 --> 18:15.572
Very funny.

18:23.493 --> 18:25.930
I found something weird
last night.

18:26.061 --> 18:29.456
Up at the attic.

18:29.586 --> 18:31.284
It's a painting.

18:31.414 --> 18:33.938
And it looks just like...

18:34.069 --> 18:35.549
Oh!

18:35.679 --> 18:37.290
I'm so sorry.

18:42.469 --> 18:44.035
You okay?

18:45.863 --> 18:48.518
There you go.

18:48.649 --> 18:50.346
Good as new.

18:58.572 --> 19:00.313
Here it is.

19:01.531 --> 19:05.013
Who's that handsome fella, huh?

19:05.144 --> 19:07.755
It's like looking
in the mirror, no?

19:07.929 --> 19:08.756
Hmm?

19:12.455 --> 19:14.240
Okay.

19:14.370 --> 19:16.459
Let's go find a memory.

19:16.590 --> 19:25.381
[♪♪♪♪]

19:39.265 --> 19:40.831
Here we go!

19:40.962 --> 19:49.884
[♪♪♪♪]

20:10.992 --> 20:19.914
[♪♪♪]

20:20.784 --> 20:23.831
[BUZZING]

20:24.048 --> 20:26.834
Hey, Brookes? Brookes?

20:28.270 --> 20:30.446
Who's got keys to the house?

20:30.577 --> 20:31.882
Just me.

20:32.056 --> 20:33.710
Were you in there last night?

20:33.841 --> 20:34.885
No.

20:35.016 --> 20:36.365
Why?

20:38.585 --> 20:40.064
Don't worry about it.

20:40.195 --> 20:49.030
[♪♪♪♪]

20:51.424 --> 20:56.429
Let's see if we can find
your cousin, Jackie and Dylan.

20:56.559 --> 20:58.169
Look over here, baby.

20:59.693 --> 21:00.346
Okay.

21:00.476 --> 21:01.608
I'll find them.

21:03.131 --> 21:05.351
Come on, Alex.

21:05.481 --> 21:07.004
Jesus.

21:15.796 --> 21:18.320
You know I'm trying to help you.

21:18.451 --> 21:20.191
That's why we're here.

21:22.933 --> 21:25.588
Let's find Calvin,
your time twin.

21:29.244 --> 21:31.464
Here we are.

21:31.594 --> 21:36.947
April 1936, Calvin painting
at the villa.

21:37.078 --> 21:38.427
There's no...

21:39.689 --> 21:40.473
Jesus!

21:40.603 --> 21:41.300
[CHUCKLES]

21:41.430 --> 21:43.040
Oh my God.

21:43.171 --> 21:44.128
Can I help you?

21:45.521 --> 21:48.132
That's first day at Princeton.

21:48.263 --> 21:50.091
I wonder what she's thinking.

21:50.221 --> 21:53.573
-SOFIA: That's you?
-Yeah. That's me.

21:53.703 --> 21:54.748
You're family?

21:54.922 --> 21:55.966
I'm Margo.

21:56.140 --> 21:57.751
Cousin Mags.

21:57.881 --> 22:00.754
-Oh.
-[MAGS LAUGHS]

22:00.884 --> 22:02.233
You're Sofia?

22:02.364 --> 22:03.670
Yes, I am.

22:03.800 --> 22:05.062
-It's nice to meet you, Sofia.
-Good to meet you, Mags.

22:05.193 --> 22:06.455
Sorry,
I didn't make the wedding.

22:06.586 --> 22:07.804
Oh.

22:07.935 --> 22:08.544
That's okay.

22:08.675 --> 22:10.503
It was just him and I.

22:10.633 --> 22:11.852
That's what he wanted.

22:11.982 --> 22:15.508
Well, with a family like ours.

22:15.638 --> 22:16.944
Aww.

22:17.074 --> 22:19.120
How are you, Alex?

22:20.426 --> 22:22.558
I heard about the accident.

22:23.603 --> 22:26.127
Damn shame.

22:26.257 --> 22:29.217
You know,
we had our knock-down-drag-outs.

22:29.348 --> 22:32.263
We couldn't agree on anything.

22:32.394 --> 22:34.570
But don't worry.

22:34.701 --> 22:36.355
You'll be back.

22:37.573 --> 22:39.880
That's the thing
about our family.

22:40.010 --> 22:42.970
We always come back.

22:43.100 --> 22:46.365
Even when they don't want us to.

22:52.675 --> 22:53.502
Hmm.

22:55.286 --> 22:56.984
Uniforms.

22:57.114 --> 22:58.681
SOFIA:
I'm sorry?

22:58.812 --> 23:00.422
Uniforms.

23:00.553 --> 23:02.946
You know,
my great-grandfather DuBose

23:03.077 --> 23:04.992
came here with a dream.

23:05.122 --> 23:08.038
Fine clothes for fine ladies.

23:08.169 --> 23:11.781
But the fine ladies didn't share
his dream.

23:13.304 --> 23:15.742
By 1914, he was sleeping
on the floor

23:15.872 --> 23:18.658
of his warehouse
eating out of a can.

23:18.832 --> 23:22.444
And then, the war happened.

23:22.575 --> 23:27.101
Uniforms, money,
and the Villa de los Sueños.

23:28.755 --> 23:30.626
Wow.

23:30.757 --> 23:32.715
I didn't know that.

23:32.846 --> 23:34.413
You know,
with a fine body like that,

23:34.543 --> 23:37.024
you could have modeled for him.

23:38.678 --> 23:39.766
[LAUGHS]

23:39.896 --> 23:41.245
MAGS:
I'm serious.

23:41.376 --> 23:43.465
You're a beautiful woman.

23:45.424 --> 23:47.730
You knew we were here.

23:47.861 --> 23:49.689
We all did.

23:49.819 --> 23:58.654
[♪♪♪♪]

24:07.620 --> 24:12.363
My grandmother hated me,
but she let me live up there.

24:12.494 --> 24:14.714
Who did you think I was?

24:14.844 --> 24:17.412
When I first came in,
you were scared.

24:18.239 --> 24:19.588
Surprised.

24:19.719 --> 24:20.546
Hmm.

24:22.896 --> 24:24.811
Did you think
I was someone else?

24:26.029 --> 24:27.596
No.

24:40.696 --> 24:42.437
What'd she take?

24:42.568 --> 24:43.177
What do you mean?

24:43.307 --> 24:43.786
[LAUGHS]

24:43.917 --> 24:45.048
She has a bag.

24:45.179 --> 24:46.441
She took something.

24:46.572 --> 24:48.835
She'd do that?

24:48.965 --> 24:50.663
Keep your doors locked.

24:55.450 --> 24:57.713
I bet you used
to play with these.

24:57.844 --> 25:06.635
[♪♪♪♪]

25:20.910 --> 25:22.695
Him?

25:25.001 --> 25:26.829
You remember him?

25:26.960 --> 25:35.795
[♪♪♪♪]

25:37.666 --> 25:39.886
Yes.

25:40.016 --> 25:41.931
You do, don't you?

25:42.062 --> 25:50.940
[♪♪♪♪]

26:10.960 --> 26:12.658
[CHUCKLES]

26:20.666 --> 26:23.538
[FIZZING]

26:29.109 --> 26:30.589
[ICE CUBES CLATTERS]

26:51.218 --> 26:54.134
[WHIRRS]

26:56.397 --> 27:05.232
[♪♪♪]

27:07.887 --> 27:11.194
♪ Oh yeah, baby ♪

27:11.325 --> 27:15.634
♪ I love you, so-o, yeah ♪

27:15.764 --> 27:16.635
♪ I'll never let you ♪

27:16.765 --> 27:18.027
♪ Baby ♪

27:18.158 --> 27:19.463
♪ I'll never let you ♪

27:19.594 --> 27:22.118
[INDISTINCT LYRICS]

27:22.249 --> 27:25.121
♪ Oh yeah, baby ♪

27:25.252 --> 27:34.174
[♪♪♪♪]

27:37.525 --> 27:40.397
[INDISTINCT LYRICS]

27:44.706 --> 27:47.883
♪ I won't lie, I'm crying ♪

27:48.014 --> 27:51.365
♪ I'll let you stay up
all night long ♪

27:51.495 --> 27:56.413
♪ Baby, I love you so-o ♪

27:56.544 --> 28:05.422
[♪♪♪♪]

28:19.262 --> 28:28.097
[♪♪♪]

28:43.417 --> 28:45.724
How's my day been?

28:45.854 --> 28:47.595
Thank you for asking.

28:51.468 --> 28:54.471
It's been good.

28:54.602 --> 28:57.387
I think we're making
some real progress here.

28:57.518 --> 28:58.867
Don't you?

29:02.392 --> 29:04.046
What was that?

29:04.177 --> 29:06.179
Yes.

29:06.309 --> 29:08.485
You were right, baby.

29:08.616 --> 29:11.184
The doctors don't know shit.

29:12.576 --> 29:15.579
We're gonna figure it out
together, aren't we?

29:20.367 --> 29:23.239
[INDISTINCT LYRICS]

29:23.370 --> 29:32.248
[♪♪♪♪]

29:53.008 --> 30:01.843
[♪♪♪]

30:21.732 --> 30:22.733
[SHATTERS]

30:28.478 --> 30:31.264
[FOOTFALLS APPROACHING]

30:34.267 --> 30:36.747
Did you do this?

30:36.878 --> 30:38.749
It's okay.

30:56.376 --> 31:05.298
[♪♪♪]

31:09.868 --> 31:12.000
I'm so sorry.

31:12.131 --> 31:20.922
[♪♪♪♪]

31:21.836 --> 31:24.621
[SIGHING]

31:24.752 --> 31:33.630
[♪♪♪♪]

31:54.825 --> 32:03.660
[♪♪♪]

32:24.855 --> 32:33.734
[♪♪♪]

32:54.842 --> 33:03.720
[♪♪♪]

33:12.338 --> 33:15.210
[GASPS]

33:21.956 --> 33:24.002
Alex?

33:27.962 --> 33:29.920
Babe?

33:30.747 --> 33:32.010
[DOOR OPENS]

33:36.753 --> 33:38.407
He was hungry,
weren't you, buddy?

33:40.409 --> 33:42.237
Hey, baby.

33:42.368 --> 33:44.065
Hey.

33:52.769 --> 33:53.857
Thank you.

33:53.988 --> 33:55.381
Don't let us keep you.

33:55.511 --> 33:56.338
BROOKES:
Oh.

33:59.124 --> 34:00.603
Hey, baby.

34:00.690 --> 34:02.301
Glad I could help out.

34:09.177 --> 34:12.050
Hey, hey.

34:22.451 --> 34:26.499
1910 to 1937.

34:26.629 --> 34:28.240
He didn't live long, did he?

34:29.502 --> 34:32.331
B.A Yale, best known
for his portraits.

34:32.461 --> 34:34.115
M.A at Col de Port,

34:34.246 --> 34:37.466
exhibit in Paris, Rome,
New York.

34:37.597 --> 34:39.294
Well, that's a big deal.

34:39.425 --> 34:48.216
[♪♪♪♪]

35:09.455 --> 35:18.290
[♪♪♪]

35:25.427 --> 35:27.473
What'd she take?

35:30.911 --> 35:32.478
You good?

35:32.608 --> 35:41.443
[♪♪♪♪]

35:49.712 --> 35:50.931
Hi.

35:51.105 --> 35:52.237
ESTHER:
Are you Sofia?

35:52.367 --> 35:53.238
Yes.

35:53.368 --> 35:56.154
Uh, this is Alex,
Margo's cousin.

35:58.939 --> 36:00.332
And you are?

36:01.507 --> 36:03.378
You got any food?

36:04.771 --> 36:06.903
Um, no, not with us.

36:08.905 --> 36:10.516
I'll go get her.

36:10.646 --> 36:19.481
[♪♪♪♪]

36:24.791 --> 36:27.533
[INDISTINCT CHATTER
IN BACKGROUND]

36:27.663 --> 36:36.585
[♪♪♪♪]

36:45.899 --> 36:47.161
MAGS:
Is everything all right?

36:47.292 --> 36:48.728
Oh, yeah.

36:48.858 --> 36:50.425
I'm-- I'm sorry,
we're intruding.

36:50.556 --> 36:51.209
No, not at all.

36:51.339 --> 36:52.775
Please.

36:58.085 --> 37:02.568
I found a painting in the attic.

37:02.698 --> 37:05.005
The self-portrait, you found it.

37:07.747 --> 37:09.227
It's Alex.

37:09.357 --> 37:10.837
Do you think so?

37:10.967 --> 37:13.231
[CHUCKLES] They're identical.

37:13.361 --> 37:15.015
MAGS:
Hmm.

37:15.145 --> 37:16.930
SOFIA:
What can you tell me
about Calvin?

37:17.060 --> 37:18.975
Calvin?

37:19.106 --> 37:21.587
Oh, why do you ask?

37:21.717 --> 37:23.850
I mean,
they're exactly the same, right?

37:23.980 --> 37:28.724
Well, all art is in the eye
of the beholder, is it not?

37:28.855 --> 37:31.640
I'm-- I'm-- I'm not talking
about art.

37:31.771 --> 37:37.646
Well, of course,
there are similarities.

37:37.777 --> 37:41.084
I mean,
we're all DuBose after all,

37:41.215 --> 37:43.696
aren't we, Alex?

37:43.826 --> 37:47.482
So why aren't there any photos
of Calvin?

37:47.613 --> 37:49.223
Because he didn't exist.

37:50.703 --> 37:52.661
According to
some family members anyway.

37:52.792 --> 37:54.097
Why?

37:56.012 --> 37:59.102
Because...

37:59.233 --> 38:02.802
Oh, oh, baby.

38:02.932 --> 38:05.195
He liked to hurt women.

38:07.720 --> 38:09.678
He was sick.

38:09.809 --> 38:13.595
But he was a genius.

38:13.726 --> 38:15.641
Not just as an artist.

38:15.771 --> 38:20.820
He was an incredible scholar
of this world and beyond.

38:20.950 --> 38:23.518
What do you mean beyond?

38:23.649 --> 38:27.609
Alex married a scientist,
didn't you?

38:27.740 --> 38:29.089
Like him, you probably think

38:29.219 --> 38:32.135
that these kind of things
are nonsense.

38:32.266 --> 38:33.485
What happened to Calvin?

38:33.615 --> 38:35.617
MAGS:
Oh, that's a good question.

38:35.748 --> 38:38.751
He hired a housekeeper.

38:38.881 --> 38:40.187
A very pretty young thing.

38:40.318 --> 38:42.668
And he became obsessed with her.

38:42.798 --> 38:46.411
And he painted her over
and over again.

38:46.541 --> 38:47.760
And then her husband died,

38:47.890 --> 38:49.283
and her grief,

38:49.414 --> 38:53.374
well, her grief to Calvin
made her even more attractive.

38:53.505 --> 38:55.507
He loves his wounded birds.

38:55.637 --> 38:57.160
Loves?

38:57.291 --> 38:58.379
He asked her--

38:58.510 --> 39:01.948
No, he told her to move it.

39:02.078 --> 39:05.212
She was already sleeping
with a young boy in town.

39:05.343 --> 39:11.392
So, the next morning,
he dragged her 4 miles,

39:11.523 --> 39:13.394
kicked in their door,

39:13.525 --> 39:15.396
raped her in front
of her lover,

39:15.527 --> 39:19.313
and then beat the two of them
to death.

39:19.487 --> 39:24.405
Us DuBose, we have
a really serious jealous streak.

39:27.756 --> 39:30.193
So Calvin?

39:30.324 --> 39:32.718
Well, the police came
and he had locked himself

39:32.848 --> 39:35.285
in his attic.

39:35.416 --> 39:40.813
They knocked down the door,
and he was gone.

39:41.683 --> 39:43.685
He escaped?

39:43.816 --> 39:45.383
Disappeared.

39:45.513 --> 39:49.691
SOFIA:
People don't just disappear.

39:49.822 --> 39:51.780
No, they don't.

39:53.565 --> 39:57.569
So, that was the last time
anyone saw him?

39:57.699 --> 40:00.615
Except in that portrait.

40:02.965 --> 40:04.227
What are you--

40:04.358 --> 40:05.751
What are you saying?

40:09.755 --> 40:12.279
The paint was still wet.

40:13.323 --> 40:16.239
[CHUCKLES]

40:17.502 --> 40:19.678
Good story.

40:19.808 --> 40:21.723
Yes, it is.

40:21.854 --> 40:22.768
[SOFIA GROANS]

40:22.898 --> 40:23.986
Something wrong, dear?

40:24.117 --> 40:25.858
We just have to get going.
Alex?

40:34.432 --> 40:36.564
I haven't seen him.

40:36.695 --> 40:38.827
Not yet.

40:38.958 --> 40:47.880
[♪♪♪♪]

40:59.587 --> 41:00.936
MAN:
You did it.

41:01.067 --> 41:09.945
[♪♪♪♪]

41:16.082 --> 41:24.960
[♪♪♪]

41:31.140 --> 41:39.975
[♪♪♪]

41:40.498 --> 41:42.064
[SIGHING]

41:42.195 --> 41:51.073
[♪♪♪♪]

42:12.268 --> 42:21.147
[♪♪♪]

42:29.851 --> 42:30.330
[KNOCKS ON THE DOOR]

42:30.460 --> 42:31.810
Jesus!

42:37.598 --> 42:40.470
[PAPERS RUSTLING]

42:43.125 --> 42:44.474
What's your name?

42:44.605 --> 42:46.738
Esther.

42:46.868 --> 42:49.349
What are we doing here, Esther?

42:49.479 --> 42:50.916
[PAPERS RUSTLING]

42:51.046 --> 42:52.526
She tells me scary stories.

42:52.657 --> 42:54.528
Mags does?

42:55.747 --> 42:57.618
Then she fucks me.

42:57.749 --> 42:59.664
She likes it better
when I'm scared.

43:01.753 --> 43:03.885
Her stories aren't true.

43:04.016 --> 43:06.148
You know that, don't you?

43:13.808 --> 43:15.157
1937.

43:18.030 --> 43:20.249
So it did happen.

43:25.211 --> 43:27.561
And Calvin did it, huh?

43:28.736 --> 43:30.912
She loves his shit.

43:37.005 --> 43:38.267
1942.

43:38.398 --> 43:40.095
Why am I looking at this?

43:40.226 --> 43:42.228
There was a war then, right?

43:42.358 --> 43:44.230
And there were soldiers up here.

43:44.360 --> 43:46.754
The sick one.

43:46.885 --> 43:47.668
But it was an accident.

43:47.799 --> 43:49.627
She fell down the stairs.

43:49.757 --> 43:51.454
The attic stairs.

43:54.457 --> 43:56.721
This one is a family friend.

43:56.851 --> 43:59.680
Ran into her screaming
one night.

43:59.811 --> 44:02.509
They found her at the bottom
of the cliff.

44:02.640 --> 44:04.903
And called it suicide.

44:10.125 --> 44:12.867
Just four years ago, that's all?

44:12.998 --> 44:16.131
She said there was more,
but the family kept '‘em quiet.

44:16.262 --> 44:18.351
Money can do that.

44:18.481 --> 44:27.273
[♪♪♪♪]

44:28.230 --> 44:30.885
You've seen him, haven't you?

44:31.016 --> 44:33.322
Seen who?

44:33.453 --> 44:35.673
Calvin.

44:35.803 --> 44:37.675
I'm tired.

44:38.937 --> 44:41.156
Please, I'm going to bed.

44:41.287 --> 44:50.209
[♪♪♪♪]

45:11.317 --> 45:20.239
[♪♪♪]

45:35.645 --> 45:37.256
What did she say?

45:37.386 --> 45:39.214
Not much.

45:39.345 --> 45:48.223
[♪♪♪♪]

46:06.415 --> 46:11.159
So Calvin, am I a wounded bird?

46:11.290 --> 46:20.212
[♪♪♪♪]

46:33.616 --> 46:36.097
[GASPS]

46:36.228 --> 46:45.063
[♪♪♪♪]

46:54.986 --> 46:56.988
EMILY ON LAPTOP:
You are pushing yourself
too hard, Fia.

46:57.118 --> 47:01.253
It's I feel like my mind's
playing tricks on me.

47:01.383 --> 47:03.211
It doesn't help that you're up
there all by yourself.

47:03.342 --> 47:05.387
I'm not here by myself, Emily.

47:05.518 --> 47:07.172
No, I know, of course.

47:07.302 --> 47:08.695
I'm sorry.

47:12.046 --> 47:13.395
You know,
in the Jewish tradition,

47:13.526 --> 47:16.094
when someone dies in the house,
we cover the mirrors.

47:16.224 --> 47:18.923
The idea is that it's no time
for vanity,

47:19.053 --> 47:23.057
but some psychologists,
myself included,

47:23.188 --> 47:26.278
think that, um,
there's another reason.

47:27.018 --> 47:28.889
We think it's so that
when you look,

47:29.020 --> 47:31.370
you don't see the face
of the dead.

47:31.500 --> 47:32.675
So you think I'm losing my mind.

47:32.806 --> 47:33.546
Is that what you're saying?

47:33.676 --> 47:35.853
No, no.

47:35.983 --> 47:38.246
I'm-- I'm saying that
there's a condition called

47:38.377 --> 47:40.161
"“pathological grief"”.

47:40.335 --> 47:44.905
It's not uncommon,
and it's-- it's powerful.

47:45.036 --> 47:47.821
So powerful that it can cause
hallucinations and visions

47:47.952 --> 47:49.344
of the ones that we lost.

47:49.475 --> 47:51.956
No, I'm--
I'm not crazy like that.

47:52.086 --> 47:54.175
No, of course not.

47:54.306 --> 47:57.700
But we're talking about grief,
okay?

47:57.831 --> 48:01.182
Deep grief that can happen
to anyone.

48:01.313 --> 48:03.532
Yeah, well,
Alex isn't dead, so...

48:03.663 --> 48:06.057
I'm just saying.

48:06.187 --> 48:07.058
Not now.

48:07.188 --> 48:08.276
Not tonight.

48:08.407 --> 48:09.669
Sorry, Em.

48:16.719 --> 48:19.244
♪ To lovers alone ♪

48:24.336 --> 48:30.342
♪ There's no space
in the countryside ♪

48:30.472 --> 48:33.954
♪ Otherwise, we could ♪

48:34.085 --> 48:36.914
[INDISTINCT LYRICS]

48:41.396 --> 48:43.137
You remember this?

48:45.966 --> 48:48.316
Come on, it's your playlist.

48:50.318 --> 48:51.667
No?

49:09.424 --> 49:10.686
I'll be right back, okay?

49:10.817 --> 49:13.646
♪ Give me a reason ♪

49:13.776 --> 49:16.649
[INDISTINCT LYRICS]

49:22.698 --> 49:26.615
♪ Maybe I'll take my chance ♪

49:28.443 --> 49:29.836
Hi.

49:31.925 --> 49:40.325
♪ Love is not given towards
without blood, sweat and tears ♪

49:40.455 --> 49:43.023
♪ Turns to dust ♪

49:43.154 --> 49:44.329
♪ It leaves ♪

49:44.459 --> 49:47.593
♪ That's what I heard ♪

49:47.723 --> 49:50.291
♪ What I heard I can trust ♪

49:55.818 --> 49:57.646
♪ Love is go... ♪

49:57.777 --> 49:59.300
JEN:
Alex?

49:59.431 --> 50:01.215
Hey.

50:03.478 --> 50:04.436
I heard what happened to you.

50:04.566 --> 50:06.133
Are you okay?

50:07.743 --> 50:08.962
[KNOCKS]

50:09.093 --> 50:10.920
Alex, it's me, Jen.

50:11.051 --> 50:13.053
You alright?

50:13.184 --> 50:15.012
♪ It's the only thing ♪

50:20.756 --> 50:23.585
[INDISTINCT LYRICS]

50:23.716 --> 50:32.638
[♪♪♪♪]

50:44.476 --> 50:46.043
Alex, hey!

50:46.173 --> 50:47.348
You okay?

50:48.828 --> 50:49.655
[THUD]

50:49.785 --> 50:52.658
Alex! No!
What are you doing?

50:52.788 --> 50:53.615
Get him out of here!

50:53.746 --> 50:54.399
Get him out!

50:54.529 --> 50:55.182
I'm so sorry.

50:57.097 --> 50:57.793
Come on.

51:03.147 --> 51:06.106
Come on, get in the car.

51:06.237 --> 51:09.109
[PANTING]

51:11.068 --> 51:13.113
Put this on.
Put this on

51:13.244 --> 51:14.462
Alex.

51:14.593 --> 51:15.550
For Christ's sake, Alex!

51:15.681 --> 51:16.769
Help me out!

51:16.899 --> 51:25.778
[♪♪♪♪]

51:46.886 --> 51:55.851
[♪♪♪]

52:23.183 --> 52:26.273
Alex? please?

52:26.404 --> 52:27.753
-Here.
-Hey!

52:27.883 --> 52:28.580
It's alright! It's alright!

52:28.710 --> 52:29.320
-I'm just--
-Alex, stop!

52:29.450 --> 52:30.016
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

52:30.147 --> 52:31.148
Stop!

52:37.023 --> 52:43.334
He's fucking crazy.

52:43.464 --> 52:45.379
Wouldn't let a dog
suffer like that.

52:45.510 --> 52:54.301
[♪♪♪♪]

52:56.782 --> 52:58.610
[SIGHS]

52:58.740 --> 53:07.619
[♪♪♪♪]

53:16.976 --> 53:19.021
Alex.

53:24.070 --> 53:25.854
I'm so sorry, baby.

53:28.117 --> 53:29.423
I'm sorry.

53:31.643 --> 53:33.645
I love you.

53:33.775 --> 53:34.689
I love you so much,

53:34.820 --> 53:36.300
but I'm running out
of ideas here.

53:36.430 --> 53:39.216
Please.

53:39.346 --> 53:41.130
Please give me a clue.

53:42.523 --> 53:44.786
Anything.

53:44.917 --> 53:46.484
I'll do anything.

53:50.662 --> 53:52.403
Please.

53:52.533 --> 53:55.406
[CRYING]

53:55.536 --> 54:04.458
[♪♪♪♪]

54:10.595 --> 54:19.430
[♪♪♪]

54:40.625 --> 54:41.016
Thank you.

54:41.147 --> 54:41.930
Yeah.

54:42.061 --> 54:44.890
Um, I'm sorry.

54:45.020 --> 54:47.240
Uh, I shouldn't have said that.

54:47.371 --> 54:49.155
How's your wrist?

54:49.286 --> 54:51.766
Oh, it's-- I'll survive.

54:51.897 --> 54:53.420
Yeah.

54:53.551 --> 54:54.943
Can I be honest?

54:55.074 --> 54:55.727
Yeah.

54:55.857 --> 54:57.076
[SIGHS]

54:57.206 --> 54:58.295
You look like you could
use a freaking break.

54:59.948 --> 55:01.515
Yeah.

55:01.646 --> 55:03.300
[SIGHS]

55:04.388 --> 55:05.780
Anything you need?

55:05.911 --> 55:07.869
No, thank you.

55:09.175 --> 55:12.265
It can help to talk,
even if it's just me.

55:16.313 --> 55:17.618
I've got vodka.

55:20.795 --> 55:22.493
Vodka it is.

55:29.456 --> 55:30.849
[CREAKS]

55:37.072 --> 55:38.683
[GULPS]

55:47.300 --> 55:50.216
[POURS]

55:53.654 --> 55:56.440
-BROOKES: Hi.
-Hi.

55:57.223 --> 55:58.311
Where is he?

55:58.442 --> 56:00.269
In his room.

56:03.142 --> 56:03.664
Here.

56:03.795 --> 56:04.926
Oh, thank you.

56:08.016 --> 56:09.235
Cheers.

56:09.366 --> 56:10.018
Cheers.

56:10.149 --> 56:12.630
And uh, good luck.

56:12.760 --> 56:14.240
[CHUCKLES]

56:21.769 --> 56:23.771
[SIGHS]

56:27.949 --> 56:29.690
You deserve it.

56:29.821 --> 56:31.518
[CHUCKLES]

56:33.215 --> 56:34.739
From your lips to God's ears.

56:35.957 --> 56:38.307
You a believer?

56:38.438 --> 56:40.701
In a God that would do
this to my husband?

56:43.095 --> 56:44.792
No.

56:44.923 --> 56:53.888
[♪♪♪♪]

56:54.846 --> 56:57.196
He's the only one that has
been there for me.

57:01.635 --> 57:06.248
And when I stray, which,
I have a lot,

57:08.381 --> 57:10.427
He leads me back.

57:15.040 --> 57:16.433
Touch it.

57:18.304 --> 57:21.394
Okay, come on, for--
for a good luck.

57:21.525 --> 57:23.527
Hmm? Go on.

57:26.399 --> 57:27.661
Yeah, here.

57:27.792 --> 57:36.627
[♪♪♪♪]

57:37.062 --> 57:38.542
Whoa!

57:39.717 --> 57:41.936
[LAUGHS]

57:43.808 --> 57:44.417
I'm sorry

57:44.548 --> 57:45.592
No.

57:47.899 --> 57:50.118
You have nothing to
be sorry for.

57:52.991 --> 57:54.688
Come on.

57:57.256 --> 57:59.214
Let him in.

58:02.000 --> 58:05.960
No, Sofia, let him in

58:06.091 --> 58:15.056
[♪♪♪♪]

58:18.451 --> 58:20.105
Don't be afraid.

58:20.235 --> 58:29.070
[♪♪♪♪]

58:32.596 --> 58:35.424
[INDISTINCT WHISPER]

58:35.555 --> 58:44.433
[♪♪♪♪]

59:05.585 --> 59:14.463
[♪♪♪]

59:18.772 --> 59:20.687
Are you okay?

59:22.733 --> 59:24.648
Come on, lets get back to bed.

59:26.084 --> 59:29.827
Alex, please.
I'm too tired for this, baby.

59:36.181 --> 59:37.225
[SCREAMS, THUDS]

59:37.356 --> 59:39.401
Alex!

59:39.532 --> 59:40.620
Please no!

59:40.751 --> 59:42.317
[PANTS] Stop.

59:42.448 --> 59:45.277
[PANTS, GROANS]

59:45.407 --> 59:54.286
[♪♪♪♪]

01:00:00.379 --> 01:00:09.301
[♪♪♪]

01:00:20.181 --> 01:00:23.097
[GASPING]

01:00:23.228 --> 01:00:32.063
[♪♪♪♪]

01:00:43.727 --> 01:00:45.206
Wake up! Wake up!

01:00:45.337 --> 01:00:46.730
We're leaving.

01:00:46.860 --> 01:00:55.913
[♪♪♪♪]

01:00:56.870 --> 01:00:58.132
EMILY ON VOICEMAIL:
You've reached
Dr. Emily Hoffman.

01:00:58.263 --> 01:00:59.656
Leave me a message
and I'll call you back.

01:00:59.786 --> 01:01:01.527
Em, It's me.

01:01:01.658 --> 01:01:05.009
Um, we're coming back.

01:01:05.139 --> 01:01:09.100
That stuff you said about
grief, and--

01:01:09.230 --> 01:01:10.884
I think I'm losing my mind.

01:01:14.583 --> 01:01:16.498
I'm taking him back
to the hospital.

01:01:20.154 --> 01:01:21.503
I-- I'll call you back.

01:01:21.634 --> 01:01:30.512
[♪♪♪♪]

01:01:55.581 --> 01:01:57.714
Brookes?

01:02:03.502 --> 01:02:05.460
Oh my God.

01:02:05.591 --> 01:02:06.723
Oh my God.

01:02:06.853 --> 01:02:15.732
[♪♪♪♪]

01:02:36.883 --> 01:02:45.762
[♪♪♪]

01:02:56.120 --> 01:03:01.386
Okay, so?

01:03:03.431 --> 01:03:06.043
I told you.

01:03:06.173 --> 01:03:08.349
I just found him out there.

01:03:08.480 --> 01:03:10.699
And your husband was
never out of your sight?

01:03:10.830 --> 01:03:12.527
That's the way we live now.

01:03:13.528 --> 01:03:16.314
You know, protecting him
isn't helping him.

01:03:16.444 --> 01:03:18.055
He doesn't need protecting.

01:03:19.273 --> 01:03:21.145
Do you?

01:03:25.062 --> 01:03:26.150
OFFICER ALVAREZ:
Sheriff?

01:03:26.280 --> 01:03:28.108
What you got?

01:03:29.196 --> 01:03:30.589
He didn't make it.

01:03:36.377 --> 01:03:37.248
I'm taking your husband in.

01:03:37.378 --> 01:03:38.815
No, why? No!

01:03:38.945 --> 01:03:40.207
You-- you've got nothing.

01:03:40.338 --> 01:03:41.687
JEN:
I've got a dead man
and another one

01:03:41.818 --> 01:03:43.210
-prone to violence.
-He's not violent.

01:03:43.341 --> 01:03:44.081
That's not who he is.

01:03:44.211 --> 01:03:45.909
JEN:
That's not who he was.

01:03:46.039 --> 01:03:47.475
I've known Alex my whole life,

01:03:47.606 --> 01:03:49.173
but even you saw
what he did to me.

01:03:49.303 --> 01:03:51.349
There's a bunch of people that
live around here.

01:03:51.479 --> 01:03:54.482
What if-- what if Brookes owed
money to the wrong person?

01:03:54.613 --> 01:03:55.875
What if he slept with
the wrong man's wife?

01:03:55.962 --> 01:03:57.921
JEN:
Did he?

01:03:58.051 --> 01:03:58.835
Fuck you.

01:03:58.965 --> 01:04:01.750
Be very careful, Miss Reyes.

01:04:01.881 --> 01:04:03.491
Brookes was hit in the head
multiple times.

01:04:03.622 --> 01:04:05.102
We don't even know how many.

01:04:05.232 --> 01:04:06.668
Never seen anything like it.

01:04:06.799 --> 01:04:09.497
Well, Alex didn't do it.

01:04:09.628 --> 01:04:11.673
JEN:
We have forensics out there,
gives us 48 hours.

01:04:11.804 --> 01:04:13.240
If we don't find anything,
he's free to go.

01:04:13.371 --> 01:04:14.502
You wanna lock him up
for two days?

01:04:14.633 --> 01:04:16.417
You've seen what he is like.

01:04:16.548 --> 01:04:17.592
JEN:
I've asked for a psychiatrist.

01:04:17.723 --> 01:04:20.813
No, no, you've--
you have no evidence.

01:04:20.944 --> 01:04:21.683
And we're leaving.

01:04:21.814 --> 01:04:23.555
Okay, you're not going anywhere.

01:04:23.685 --> 01:04:24.469
Listen to me.

01:04:24.599 --> 01:04:26.732
It's my job to protect people.

01:04:26.863 --> 01:04:29.169
Protect whom?
Hmm?

01:04:29.300 --> 01:04:31.345
-Who's he gonna hurt?
-JEN: You.

01:04:33.782 --> 01:04:37.525
Well, then that's
a risk I'm willing to take.

01:04:37.656 --> 01:04:40.702
But you lock him up,
and you'll send him

01:04:40.833 --> 01:04:42.835
to a place he might
never come back from.

01:04:42.966 --> 01:04:45.882
JEN:
Miss Reyes, I understand
you have been through--

01:04:46.012 --> 01:04:48.232
You know this family, right?

01:04:48.362 --> 01:04:49.842
You said you did.

01:04:51.626 --> 01:04:53.411
So you know the kind
of money they've got.

01:04:55.630 --> 01:04:57.110
You do this.

01:04:57.241 --> 01:04:59.112
You meet their lawyers.

01:05:00.461 --> 01:05:02.289
So please.

01:05:05.162 --> 01:05:06.337
Please.

01:05:13.039 --> 01:05:13.779
JEN:
I'm leaving my deputy here.

01:05:13.910 --> 01:05:14.911
You don't have to do that.

01:05:15.041 --> 01:05:16.303
JEN:
